body:
Hey guys,

So I decided to make a new logo for Avicus and that one didn't turn out so well so I have decided to make a new one! This one took 1 hour to make and about 2 1/2 hours searching for the right material to include in it. Now I have noticed that every single thing I make gets hate, now I am please asking for as less hate as possible :) That would make my day!!

Here it is!

or you can view it on imgur: http://imgur.com/oVkAv0c

I put in a lot of hard work to get this done and looking as quality as possible so I hope you enjoy it and please as less hate as possible and constructional criticism!

Cheers!
- Sheamus

replies.body:
this is a cool concept for a banner, it looks like you put effort into it and all. the next stuff isn't meant to be rude but to offer the constructive criticism. if you work on this pic a bit more it could be a cool background, but logos are usually very simplistic.
avicus has a minimalistic logo, just two simplified letters, and it looks great.


if you really do want feedback, i would say that the pasted in stuff in the background doesn't look smooth, i would take the individual images like the light orb and go in with a very small, very light eraser and just feather out the edges to make the transition better. the edges of the blue circle look rough, and the other background elements could use some work in that area. second, the fonts- a couple small tweaks could make them better. try downloading more customized fonts rather than using papyrus and other default fonts. the words at the bottom are good, but i would make them all much smaller, perfectly evened up next to each other, and i would give the "enjoyable" an icon like the log/apple.

also, generally with this kind of design process you wanna make the colors balanced. these are kind of all over the place. orange and blue really clash, it's best to stick with one color and maybe a couple others that look good with it. the swords could be crossed in an "X" and below the words "the avicus network", that might make the pic more balanced.

it's good, but it could use a little work. don't take what people say here too badly, if you wanna make good art it takes a long time to get to know what looks good. i've been doing art for a long time and i still havent gotten it down, but i don't give up when it gets hard, i take a little break and then get back at it.
